    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweetcorn-chana-curry-with-tomato-and-coriander-salad-and-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>sweetcorn cobettes</strong> coarsely</p><p>Tip: Grate the cobettes right down to the core</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweetcorn-chana-curry-with-tomato-and-coriander-salad-and-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your<strong> creamed</strong> <strong>coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> coconut stock</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweetcorn-chana-curry-with-tomato-and-coriander-salad-and-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced shallot </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once slightly softened, add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>with your <strong>ground coriander</strong>, <strong>ground cumin </strong>and <strong>garam masala </strong>and cook for a further 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweetcorn-chana-curry-with-tomato-and-coriander-salad-and-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>grated sweetcorn </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the sweetcorn is slightly creamy</p><p>Add the <strong>drained chickpeas </strong>and <strong>coconut stock </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for a further 6-7 min or until the sauce has thickened slightly</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweetcorn-chana-curry-with-tomato-and-coriander-salad-and-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the curry is cooking, finely dice your <strong>tomato[es]</strong></p><p>Chop most of your<strong> coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks (reserve a few leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Combine the <strong>diced tomatoes </strong>and <strong>chopped coriander </strong>in a bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato & coriander salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweetcorn-chana-curry-with-tomato-and-coriander-salad-and-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach </strong>and pat it dry with kitchen paper, then chop it roughly</p><p>Stir the <strong>chopped spinach</strong> through the curry and stir it all together for 1-2 min or until wilted \u2013 this is your <strong>sweetcorn chana curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweetcorn-chana-curry-with-tomato-and-coriander-salad-and-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sweetcorn chana curry </strong>over the <strong>basmati</strong> <strong>rice </strong>with the <strong>tomato & coriander salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Top with a dollop of <strong>mango chutney </strong>and garnish with the <strong>reserved coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
